beer_name: Stillwater / Hof Ten Dormaal Bronze Age

review_blob:
Big foamy brown head. Lots of chocolate with a great creamy mouthfeel. There is some slight bitterness that adds nice depth. Great milk stout!


---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Giant head and big coffee aroma. Tons of coffee on the first sip, followed by some nice bitter cocoa. A little too light in body but very nice. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This thick syrupy beer still has an aroma that would knock an elephant back.  Bold and intense, loads of oak and apples on the nose.  The first sip is extremely intense, but further tastes open this up into a beautifully complex drink, loaded with fruits, oak and funky malt.  A pleasure.

Bottle. Very little carbonation here. Dark dark brown color. Aroma rich and full of malt and caramel and oak. Tasteis complex and big up front but backs off the gas with a lighter and cleaner finish than you would expect. Not too syrupy, just right.
Bottle.  Massive beige head. Heady malty caramel aroma. Creamy as it pours, dark brown after settling. Caramel and bread core with a mildly bitter finish. Excellent brew.
Bottle. Light head with decent amount of carbonation. Malty but crisp and not a lot of depth. Some nice yeast qualities - great for outdoors.

beautifully dark, with a little brown head.  The aroma is rich with barrel and chocolate.  The taste, is surprise equally malty and hoppy.  I shared this with a few friends and we all marveled at the hop character that we got out of this.  Lighter mouth-feel than i expected in a RIS, but a remarkably interesting beer.
beer_name: Nebraska Reserve Series Black Betty Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: I really tried to not let my opinion of Shiner weigh in on this one.  It looked proper enough, pretty light brown clear color with little head.  Then i smelled the beer - honestly smells of day old beer - heavy alcohol smell.   The taste was very domestic-y with hardly any wheat character discernible.  Not good.

This hazy golden concoction is anything but what you would expect from this low abv brew.  High carbonation, big foamy head, but a wonderfully light and crisp flavor with a hint of breadiness that makes you think is a normal beer - rather than the ultra-session beer that it is?  Mikkeller amazes me again.
